            "abstract": "Crystal storing histiocytosis is a rare disorder associated with monoclonal gammopathy. In this disease, monoclonal heavy and light chains accumulate in the lysosome of macrophages, leading to histiocytic reaction in different organs. It is secondary to the presence of a small B-cell clone, responsible for monoclonal immunoglobulin production. Histological diagnosis is a challenge and differential diagnoses include fibroblastic and histiocytic neoplasm. Clinical manifestations depend on the involved organs, rarely including peritoneum or digestive tract.",
